<BR><BR> FIG. 2 is a bar graph illustrating the effects of racemic verapamil HCl, (R)-(+)-verapamil HCl and (S)-(-)-verapamil HCl on the level of blood glucose in NIDDM mice in accordance with Example 1.2 of this invention;
<BR><BR> FIG. 3 is a bar graph illustrating the effects of (R)-(+)-verapamil HCl and/or metformin on the level of blood glucose in NIDDM mice in accordance with Example 2.1 of this invention, in which differences are considered significant at
.dagger.&lt;0.05, vs vehicle control (db/m+), *P&lt;0.05, vs vehicle control (db/db), #P&lt;0.05, vs metformin (db/db).  Comparisons of "metformin" and "vehicle control (db/db" is performed using Student's unpaired t-test: significance denoted by solid
lines; and
